        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a Chinese translation of the contributing guide to help Chinese speaking contributors understand the contribution process and guidelines\n- Covers how to contribute, PR limits, before you PR checklist, code style guidelines, AI-assisted PR guidelines, and current focus/roadmap\n- Improves accessibility for Chinese speaking contributors\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nOpenClaw has a growing Chinese speaking community. Adding a Chinese contributing guide will help these contributors understand the contribution process and guidelines more easily, potentially increasing the number and quality of contributions from Chinese speaking developers.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Positive: Chinese speaking contributors can now read the contributing guide in their native language\n- No negative impact: The original English guide remains unchanged\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Created `docs/contributing-zh.md` with Chinese translation of the contributing guide\n- Translation covers all key sections from the original English guide\n- Maintains the same structure and formatting as the original\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncat docs/contributing-zh.md | head -50\n```\n\nThe Chinese guide includes all essential sections:\n- How to contribute\n- PR limits\n- Before you PR checklist\n- Code style guidelines\n- AI-assisted PR guidelines\n- Current focus and roadmap",
